Highly organized, capable of working on multiple projects at once

Important to have: Advanced knowledge of international financial markets such as asset allocation, equity ratings, macroeconomic conditions, quantitative and algorithmic trading, retail and institutional brokerages, investment management, macroeconomic forecasts, capital market assumptions and outlook, as well as overall fundamental and technical research and ability to identify prospects in search for our research; understanding of local brokers and investment mangers, wealth managers, RIA's and others based on each jurisdiction; strong understanding of risk across all asset classes, across local and international instruments;

Good to have: Brokerage accounts with multiple institutions for a clear understanding of local offering, such as local market data, investment research and other offerings; a track record of either having participated, or currently participating in short term, medium term, long term investments in public markets; knowledge of a variety of instruments such as futures, options, derivatives;

Also good to have: certifications such as CFA, CFP, CIM, RFP, FMVA, CAIA, CPA, FRM and former or current work experience in the investment management field at both the institutional level as well as the retail level;

